        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 11:50PM EDT by NWS Newport/Morehead City NC</headline>
        <description>At 1149 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Bruce, or 8 miles north of Farmville, moving
southwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Farmville, Bruce, Fountain, Bull Head VFD, Walstonburg, and Falkland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
